11/12/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The Belgrade District Court on Thursday (December 10th) sentenced a football fan to 30 years in prison for murder of a rival team's fan. 
Bojan Hrvatin, 24, was a member of the Rad club's fan group, which used knives to attack the Vozdovac team's fan group at a Belgrade railway station on August 4th 2006. 
Hrvatin was found guilty of stabbing the victim to death. 
Three other Rad fans received sentences ranging from one to three years for taking part in the fight. 
(Beta, B92, RTS, AP - 10/12/09)
